# No issue IDs in source

- **Never** put tracker references in application code: no `WALLET-105`, `REF-001`, `GH-123`, Jira keys, or similar in:
  - comments and docblocks
  - string literals (including user-visible copy)
  - inline `//` / `/* */` next to implementations
- Describe behavior in plain language only (e.g. “focus trap; restore focus on close”).
- Use **tracked design docs** under `docs/` (e.g. `docs/wallet/`) for anything linked from code or user-visible strings. Keep internal checklists or scratch notes out of `src/`, `src-tauri/`, scripts, and shipped config; optional private doc trees (e.g. gitignored) must not be the only home for paths cited in the repo.

```ts
// ❌ BAD
/** Modal focus trap (see WALLET-105). */

// ✅ GOOD
/** Modal: focus trap and restore previous focus on close. */
```
